    <title>Fair Access to Science and Technology Research Act of 2017</title>
    <updateDate>2019-04-18T16:13:43Z</updateDate>
    <billType>HR</billType>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2017-07-26</actionDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-08-08T18:11:09Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Fair Access to Science and Technology Research Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill requires each federal agency with extramural research expenditures of over $100 million to develop a federal research public access policy that is consistent with, and that advances, the purposes of the agency and that follows common procedures for the collection and depositing of research papers. </p> <p>Each federal research public access policy is applicable to: (1) researchers employed by the federal agency whose works remain in the public domain, and (2) researchers funded by the agency. The bill specifies exclusions.</p> <p>Each federal agency must submit an annual report on its federal research public access policy to specified congressional committees.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-07-26T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
